" Complete development milestones for autonomous systems within defined timelines and resource constraints.
1. Modular Software Architecture
1.1 Design and implement a modular software architecture that supports scalable UI and mission-control systems, ensuring clear interface definitions, decoupled components, and standardized communication protocols across all subsystems.
A. Unmanned Aerial Vehicle
Technologies: C++, OpenCV
2.1 Implement object identification and tracking using computer vision techniques
2.2 Integrate a trajectory planning module with velocity profiling
2.3 Generate trajectory points along X and Y axes for path planning
2.4 Enable smooth and accurate path execution for autonomous navigation
2.5 Enhance dynamic response to detected objects in real time
B. Ground-Based Autonomous  Vehicle
Technologies: PyQt, Python, C++
Key Deliverables:
1.1 Authentication & Authorization: Role-based access control using SQLite; user provisioning for operators, maintenance, and general users
1.2 Connection Settings: Real-time configuration panels for Wi-Fi, Ethernet, and Serial interfaces
1.3 Power-On Self-Test (POST): Automated diagnostics and readiness checks at startup
1.4 Peripheral Testing: Pre/Post test automation for PTZ, motor, battery, and GNSS modules
1.5 GO / NO GO Decision: POST-based mission readiness evaluation logic
1.6 Mission Planning UI: DSM & Survey of India map integration for mission visualization
1.7 GCS Parameters Panel: Waypoint, speed, and mode configuration interface
1.8 Communication Protocols: Defined command list and message formats
1.9 Data Exchange: MAVLink/ROS-based bidirectional communication between GCS and UGV
1.10 Notifications & Alerts: Health threshold alerts, emergency triggers, and pop-up warnings
1.11 System Health Assessment: Real-time diagnostics and scoring system
1.12 Fault Management: Rule-based fault classification and prioritization
1.13 Emergency Management: Sensor-driven automation for emergency scenarios
C. Kalyani Autonomous Underwater Vehicle
Technologies: C++, Python, Qt
Key Contributions:
2.1 Team Enablement: Delivered Qt module training to peers
2.2 Mission Editor Design: Developed class diagrams and UI for mission planning
2.3 Mission Dialog UI: Tabbed interface for Mission, Live Tracking, and Replay
2.4 Settings Panel: Integrated unit-aware manual input fields (e.g., WP Speed, Altitude)
2.5 Waypoint Programming:
2.5.1 Add/Remove/Clear waypoints with coordinate input and visual feedback
2.5.2 Map loading and mission file management (Save/Upload)
2.6 Mission Controls: Launch, Abort, Cancel, and Save functionalities
2.7 Live Tracking:
2.7.1 Real-time AUV simulation with dynamic plotting of waypoints
2.7.2 Speed, location, and heading visualization
2.8 Authentication & Authorization: SQLite-based role management
2.9 Navigation Module:
2.9.1 High-Level Design (HLD) for mission planning and control
2.9.2 Low-Level Design (LLD) for heading, depth, and speed regulation
2.10 Replay Module: Designed playback system for mission data
2.11 Code Optimization: Refactored Mission and Live Tracking modules for modularity
2.12 Bug Fixes: Resolved signal-slot issues, compilation errors, and event handling bugs
2.13 User Testing & Documentation: Conducted usability testing, created manuals, and training materials"
